wikipedia_page.main: Sir John Ross, 1st Baronet, PC (I), KC (1853–1935) was an Irish politician and  judge who was the last person to hold the office of Lord Chancellor of Ireland.

response: * Sir John Ross, 1st Baronet (1853–1935), Irish judge and Unionist politician

He was the only son of Sir John Ross, 1st Baronet, the last judge to hold the office of Lord Chancellor of Ireland, and Katherine Mary Jeffcock. He succeeded to the title on his father's death in 1935.
